    "body": "I think what OP want is to have the stdout of `forge test`, but at the same time, save the output of `forge test --json` to a file.\r\n\r\nTo implement that, we could save the output of serialized `results` to a file [here](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/c192620d406f4b01ee4fcc02dfc6eceeda1031e9/cli/src/cmd/forge/test.rs#L618) and [here](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/c192620d406f4b01ee4fcc02dfc6eceeda1031e9/cli/src/cmd/forge/test.rs#L735) if the `--json-file` flag is supplied?",
